{
  "stem": "16571.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I understand that, obviously, I stayed with them, and I met a lot of the boys who were originally in England, and they were in-- in America.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I went to my auntie, and I had some of my friends.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were invited to dinner.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was about 14 or 16 people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I was talking for a change.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I always talk.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And suddenly, it all went quiet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I said, what's that?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What's happened?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why has everybody gone quiet?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We do love the way you talk English, Steve.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was-- and my-- my accent is, I-- I claim, I was taught English in Scotland by German refugees who came over before the war.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But really, I never had a proper lesson.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I might have stayed once or twice, with a blackboard outside, I might say, a lovely summer, outside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [BACKROUND NOISE] it wasn't until many years later that I found out that this-- what's her name's-- my-- that-- you know, I'm-- I'm-- I'm mixing myself up.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We were talking at this table, and they said to me-- he's probably falling asleep-- they said to me, Steve, how come you're a jeweler?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I said, well, I was going to come to America.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was going-- I was-- My uncle was being a jeweler, and I was-- thought, if I come here, I will-- I'll be able to work for him, or if not for him, he might know somebody else who-- He said, what are you talking about?",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Your uncle was never a jeweler.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He wasn't the [? smartest. ?] I said, it just shows you by shear fate, I became a jeweler, because they made out at the Jewish Refugee Committee, that I-- that my uncle was a jeweler, from the half-address I gave him.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
